comments: Mann (OKC) maintains a legal dribble and does not bring his hand underneath the ball during his dribble drive.
Banchero (ORL) makes some contact with Mann's (OKC) forearm after the release of the driving shot attempt. The contact on the play is marginal.
Mann (OKC) reaches in and makes contact to the ball and marginal contact to Wagner's (ORL) side in transition.
Pokusevski (OKC) legally contests Suggs's (ORL) jump shot attempt.
Mann (OKC) establishes himself in Wagner's (ORL) path and does not deliver illegal contact during the pick.
Suggs (ORL) moves alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Bol (ORL) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Banchero (ORL) establishes himself in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and does not deliver contact as Gilgeous-Alexander goes over the pick.
Dort (OKC) reaches in for the ball and makes contact with Wagner's (ORL) leg and shoulder, which affects his SQBR.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and Wagner (ORL) engage and disengage away from the ball and the contact is marginal.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) momentarily brings his left arm around Carter Jr.'s (ORL) side as the player disengage from the pick. The contact during the disengage is marginal.
Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes himself in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs as Gilgeous-Alexander attempts to get over the pick.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) makes marginal contact to Wagner's (ORL) side prior to dislodging the ball away.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) makes contact with the ball and part of Wagner's (ORL) hand that is on the ball, which dislodges it from Wagner's grasp during his upward shooting motion.
Mann (OKC) makes contact with Carter Jr.'s (ORL) arm, which affects his attempt at the basket.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) moves towards Wagner (ORL) and then retreats away from the defender and does not deliver any contact.

Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes himself in a screening position in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and Carter Jr. lightly brushes the defender's back as he releases away from Gilgeous-Alexander. The contact on the play is marginal.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) momentarily places a hand on Wagner's (ORL) side and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes himself in Mann's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs as Mann moves over the screen.
Pokusevski (OKC) avoids making contact with Bol (ORL) and cleanly deflects Wagner's (ORL) pass.
Suggs (ORL) has his foot planted on the ground and incidental contact occurs between the ball and his leg during Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) dribble.
Suggs (ORL) goes to the ground in pursuit of the loose ball and avoids making contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC), who is able to recover the ball.
Wagner (ORL) commits a take foul on Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path and does not deliver any contact while setting the pick.
Dort (OKC) moves alongside Banchero (ORL) and absorbs the marginal contact as he retreats during the driving shot attempt.

Banchero's (ORL) arm lightly brushes Robinson-Earl's (OKC) face as the players return to the floor and the contact during the rebound is marginal. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Correctly called twenty-four second violation.
